{
  "stem": "25639.9",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was established when I got there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were some-- there were just really a couple of other girls who were a few months older, or maybe a year older, than I was.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was one girl from Czechoslovakia was only about six, seven months older than I was.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But all the others were older.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And later, when I returned to Malmo, I went to visit the cemetery, and there were rows and rows of gravestones.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I have-- I've-- we filmed these stones-- 60 millimeter of film-- we have them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And some-- some stones give their first names, others both, and if they had the date of birth, they-- they have it on it, and where they are from.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But they all give limited bits of information about them and there were many more than I-- than I really thought.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Eventually, a monument was put up in-- in the cemetery for the victims of the Holocaust from the European countries that were affected.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It's a beautiful monument, right next to the synagogue-- well, across the street from the synagogue in Malmo, Sweden.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The people who were buried there were those who were rescued by Count Folke Bernadotte, and they just didn't-- didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They died on the way or after.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, the Swedish family was just superb.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My Swedish foster father, we-- I called him Farbror Eric.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Farbror means-- 'far' is part of the word, means father, Eric is his first name-- and it designates that he's father's brother.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I called it-- it's-- it's equivalent to an uncle.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So Farbror Eric.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
